  <static seed="31" source="Contrib/PCC/BasicAlgebra/FractionArithmetic/MultiplyFractions30.pg">
    <statement><p>Multiply: <m>\displaystyle{7\cdot \frac{3}{8} }</m></p>
<p><fillin characters="11" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>{\frac{21}{8}}</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>To multiply an integer with a fraction, first we change the integer into a fraction by rewriting it with a <lq/>1<rq/> as the denominator:</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{7 = \frac{7}{1} }</m></p>
<p>Next, simply multiply both numerators and both denominators:</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\begin{aligned}[t]
   7\cdot \frac{3}{8} 
       \amp = \frac{7}{1} \cdot \frac{3}{8} \\
       \amp = \frac{7\cdot3}{1 \cdot 8} \\
       \amp = \frac{21}{8}
\end{aligned}
    }</m></p>
<p>The answer to this question is <m>\displaystyle{\frac{21}{8}}</m>.</p>
</solution>
